
Replace `<your-username>` with your GitHub username.

## 📌 Hosting Instructions

### Option A: GitHub Pages (Recommended)
1. Add `privacy.html` at the root of this repository.  
2. Go to **Settings → Pages** in this repo.  
3. Under *Source*, select `main` branch → `/ (root)`.  
4. Save.  
5. GitHub Pages will provide a public URL where your privacy policy is hosted.  

### Option B: Google Drive
1. Upload `privacy.html` to Google Drive.  
2. Right-click → Share → set to “Anyone with the link → Viewer”.  
3. Use a Drive-to-web hosting service if needed.  

### Option C: Any Web Host / Notion
1. Publish `privacy.html` to your own website, hosting service, or Notion page.  
2. Copy the public link.  

## 📬 Use in Chrome Web Store
Take the link from one of the hosting methods above and paste it into the **Privacy Policy URL** field of your Chrome Web Store Developer Console under the **Privacy tab**.

